Lists in jQuery (specifically in jQuery Mobile) are enhanced versions of standard HTML lists that provide touch-friendly styling, navigation support, icons, and formatting. jQuery Mobile converts `<ul>` or `<ol>` elements into **listviews**, which are used for menus, navigation items, and grouped content on mobile interfaces.

A jQuery Mobile list becomes interactive when you apply `data-role="listview"`. It automatically gains padding, touch highlighting, arrow indicators, and structured formatting. You can include icons, thumbnails, nested lists, and split buttons. Lists are essential for building mobile menus, settings screens, and category-based displays.

**How to Divide Lists**

jQuery Mobile supports **list dividers** to group list items under labeled headings. Dividers are created by adding `data-role="list-divider"` to a `<li>` inside the list. These dividers are styled differently and act as non-clickable section headers. List division is useful when categorizing content alphabetically, by type, or by any logical grouping.

Example of dividing a list:

```html
<ul data-role="listview">
  <li data-role="list-divider">Fruits</li>
  <li>Apple</li>
  <li>Mango</li>

  <li data-role="list-divider">Vegetables</li>
  <li>Carrot</li>
  <li>Potato</li>
</ul>
```

In this example, “Fruits” and “Vegetables” act as visual separators.
Dividers improve readability and organization, especially in longer lists.

